sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant HTTP as HTTP Server (FastAPI)<br/>8080/TCP Optional TLS
    participant GRPC as gRPC Server<br/>8085/TCP Optional TLS/mTLS
    participant Predict as GlobalPredictServicer
    participant Train as GlobalTrainServicer
    participant ModelMgr as ModelManager
    participant Model as LoadedModel<br/>(Module.run)
    participant MMesh as Model Mesh Controller
    participant MRServicer as ModelRuntimeServicer
    participant Loader as CoreModelLoader
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    rect rgb(230, 245, 255)
        Note over Client, Model: Flow 1: Model Inference (HTTP)
        Client->>HTTP: POST /api/v1/{task}/{model_id}<br/>HTTP/HTTPS, Optional TLS
        HTTP->>Predict: Route to servicer<br/>(in-process)
        Predict->>ModelMgr: Retrieve loaded model<br/>(in-process)
        ModelMgr->>Model: Module.run(request)<br/>(in-process)
        Model-->>ModelMgr: Prediction result
        ModelMgr-->>Predict: Result
        Predict-->>HTTP: Response
        HTTP-->>Client: JSON response or SSE stream<br/>HTTP/HTTPS
    end

    rect rgb(230, 255, 230)
        Note over Client, Model: Flow 2: Model Inference (gRPC)
        Client->>GRPC: {TaskName}Service RPC<br/>gRPC, Optional TLS/mTLS
        GRPC->>Predict: CaikitRuntimeServerWrapper<br/>(interceptor routing)
        Predict->>ModelMgr: Retrieve loaded model<br/>(in-process)
        ModelMgr->>Model: Module.run(request)<br/>(in-process)
        Model-->>ModelMgr: Prediction result
        ModelMgr-->>Predict: Result
        Predict-->>GRPC: gRPC response
        GRPC-->>Client: gRPC response<br/>Optional TLS/mTLS
    end

    rect rgb(255, 245, 230)
        Note over MMesh, S3: Flow 3: Model Loading via Model Mesh
        MMesh->>MRServicer: loadModel(modelId, modelPath)<br/>gRPC via Unix socket or 8085/TCP
        MRServicer->>ModelMgr: load_model(model_id, path)<br/>(in-process)
        ModelMgr->>Loader: load(model_path)<br/>(in-process)
        Loader->>S3: Download model artifacts<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS, IAM Auth
        S3-->>Loader: Model artifacts
        Loader-->>ModelMgr: Loaded module instance
        ModelMgr-->>MRServicer: Model ready
        MRServicer-->>MMesh: LoadModelResponse(sizeInBytes)
    end

    rect rgb(255, 230, 245)
        Note over Client, Model: Flow 4: Training Job
        Client->>HTTP: POST /api/v1/{module}/train<br/>HTTP/HTTPS, Optional TLS
        HTTP->>Train: Route to servicer<br/>(in-process)
        Train->>Model: Module.train(data) [async]<br/>(in-process, background thread)
        Note right of Model: Training runs<br/>asynchronously
        Model-->>Train: Training ID
        Train-->>HTTP: Training ID + status
        HTTP-->>Client: {"training_id": "...", "status": "RUNNING"}

        Client->>HTTP: GET /api/v1/training/status/{id}<br/>HTTP/HTTPS (polling)
        HTTP-->>Client: {"status": "COMPLETED", "model_id": "..."}
    end
